    {
        "content": "<p>Does this make \"AAA\" as type ABC or does the first example just prove \"AAA\" is in the set ABC.</p>",
        "id": 467649224,
        "sender_full_name": "Colin Jones ⚛️",
        "timestamp": 1725480130
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would like to change \"AAA\" into type ABC if possible aka <code>#check \"AAA\"</code> outputs ABC</p>",
        "id": 467649522,
        "sender_full_name": "Colin Jones ⚛️",
        "timestamp": 1725480216
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For that, you should make it a def and assign it a name.  For instance</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">aaa</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ABC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"s2\">\"AAA\"</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">aaa</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 467650206,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1725480391
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Okay, is there a way to transfer between types e.g. <code>#check (\"AAA\" : ABC)</code> like <code>#check (1 : ℤ)</code>.</p>",
        "id": 467650972,
        "sender_full_name": "Colin Jones ⚛️",
        "timestamp": 1725480607
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think that you can: somewhere there has to be a check that the string that you are using satisfies your predicate.</p>",
        "id": 467654605,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1725481908
    }
